pgTitle: List of World War II films 1950–1989

rows.text: Comedy. Hungarian soldiers attempt to surrender to Soviet army
McHale's Navy Joins the Air Force
German in India blackmailed by British to impersonate SS officer aboard cargo ship bound for Germany
US and Japanese soldiers temporarily unite to survive on isolated Pacific Island
Filipino guerrillas battle remaining Japanese forces
Allied POWs escape from Italian camps by train
Don't Look Now... We're Being Shot At!
Comedy. RAF crew attempt escape through occupied France aided by two Frenchmen
US commandos infiltrate German lines in northern France, 1945
Romance/Drama. Japanese nurse serves in field hospitals of China
What Did You Do in the War, Daddy?
Adventure. US corporal, priest, and Filipino children flee the Japanese
Polish resistance during German occupation of Poland, 1943
Rassenschande: When Love Was a Crime
Canadian officer guides British and German-Jewish commandos to destroy Tobruk fuel storage, September 1942
Comedy-drama. Jewish boy sent to live on farm during German occupation of France
Italian-American soldiers disguised in Italian uniform infiltrate North African camp
Testa di sbarco per otto implacabili (Italian)
Downed US Marine pilot and marooned Japanese Navy captain on deserted Pacific island
Former USAAF pilots forced to work for international smuggler in North Africa to earn money needed for return to civilian life, 1946
Allied undercover agents aided by Polish resistance on mission to stop Nazis from developing "super torpedo"
Drama based on director's diary. Young German's flight from Nazis to Moscow and return to Berlin as Russian Army officer
British paratroopers separated from regiment take German officer prisoner
Riders in the Sky (Sky Riders / Heaven Riders)
The Secret War of Harry Frigg
Comedy. Escape of Allied Generals held in special Italian camp
The Battle of the Last Panzer (The Last Panzer Battalion)
Surviving German tank crew attempt to reach friendly lines
La caduta degli dei (Italian) Die Verdammten (German)
Wealthy industrialist family during Hitler's rise to power
Polish resistance and Soviet partisans in Poland, 1944
British officers pursue Nazi saboteurs through London
Comedy-drama. Oddball US commandos with mission behind enemy lines
How I Unleashed the Second World War
British female officers infiltrate Nazi internment camp to reach inmate scientist
Salt in the Wound (The Dirty Two)
Condemned US soldiers survive Nazi ambush on way to execution and defend Italian village from invading Germans
Aftermath of fall of Mussolini's Fascist government
Largest air armada on daytime mission targets German fighter plane production
Wake Me When the War Is Over
Small units in North African desert battle, and French villa raid
